- PIP gets installed by default when you download and install python in your system.
- PIP is standard pkg manager for python it allows us to install and manage the additional packages which are not part
of Python standard library.
- PIP download and install, injects the pkgs directly into the Python virtual env i.e., venv
- It installs them by default in lib under site-packages

- to install specific version of a pkg
    pip install selenium==3.141.0
